Synopsis:
DEPRECATED, though some nodes are reused in CAMP_OwlbearCub_CRD_2_aaccfa43-76c2-b9b2-1415-1377def80251 In SwA, the owlbear cub speaks in short staccato 'sentences.' He's vicious and feral, though less so in this dialogue than in the previous two - he's become mellowed and tentatively views the player as a potential friend. If the player has not 'befriended' him by this point, he will start out scared but will quickly become excited to give you a present - a dead bird. If the player plays their cards right (by eating the bird, convincing him they've eaten the bird, or by tactfully letting him eat it instead), the cub decides the camp could be his new home. The owlbear has appeared in camp for a third night. The player has previously spared the cub after killing its mother, and saved it from a cruel game run by the goblins in their camp. He reacts much more suspiciously of the player if they antagonised him in either of their previous encounters. If players are nice to him, he reveals that he's caught a dead bird, and offers it to the players to eat.

Synopsis:
Unfortunate gnome's dialog after the goblin hunt celebration party. There are actually two different dialoues: one for when the player sided with the goblins, in which he is pissed off at the player and ready to leave, and one where the player sided with the tieflings, in which he is happy for them, but doesn't want to partake in the celebrations himself, since it has nothing to do with him, and he wants to go save his friend as soon as possible. In this case, he's standing next to a workbench, working on making explosive arrows.

Synopsis:
The goblin king is about to conduct a ceremony in which he speak's with a mind flayer's dead body. He is a hobgoblin on a power trip, but still devoted to his god The Absolute. Like most goblins, he's not greatly intelligent, but a cut above the rest. Pronunciation: Dror Ragzlin = Drawer RAGS-lin. Z'Rell = Zuh-RELL. Other prinunciations in actor node field. Goblin language words should sound guttural and trashy. When they engage with Ragzlin, the player will experience a brief vision of him with an elf - this is teasing Ketheric Thorm, a later antagonist. Ragzlin will say he's looking for a weapon - the place will realise via narrator or mindmeld with Shadowheart that this is the gith artefact that she has.

Synopsis:
The goblin king is about to conduct a ceremony in which he speak's with a mind flayer's dead body. He is a hobgoblin on a power trip, but still devoted to his god The Absolute. Like most goblins, he's not greatly intelligent, but a cut above the rest. Pronunciation: Dror Ragzlin = Drawer RAGS-lin. Z'Rell = Zuh-RELL. Other prinunciations in actor node field. Goblin language words should sound guttural and trashy. When they engage with Ragzlin, the player will experience a brief vision of him with an elf - this is teasing Ketheric Thorm, a later antagonist. Ragzlin will say he's looking for a weapon - the place will realise via narrator or mindmeld with Shadowheart that this is the gith artefact that she has.
